  m_text: "\n\n\n\n\nDriving Simulator Prototype \u2013 Terms & Conditions\r\n\r\n1.
    Educational Purpose Only\r\nThis simulator is intended for educational and practice
    purposes only. It is designed to help users learn and reinforce safe driving
    practices. It does not replace real driving instruction or testing, and completing
    this simulation does not grant a driving license.\n\r\n2. Scope & Limitations\r\n\t\u2022
    The content of this simulator is based on Irish driving laws, signage, and procedures.\r\n\t\u2022
    It may not reflect driving rules in other countries.\r\n\t\u2022 Some scenarios
    are simplified and may not capture all real-world complexities.\n\r\n3. Safety
    Disclaimer\r\n\t\u2022 The simulator is not a substitute for actual driving experience.\r\n\t\u2022
    Users should never attempt maneuvers from the simulation in real life without
    proper instruction and supervision.\r\n\t\u2022 The simulator cannot replicate
    real-world hazards such as weather conditions, pedestrians, or unpredictable
    driver behavior.\n\r\n4. Prototype Status\r\n\t\u2022 This software is a prototype
    and may contain incomplete, simplified, or experimental features.\r\n\t\u2022
    Functionality and scenarios may change as the project develops.\n\r\n5. User
    Responsibility\r\nBy using this simulator, you acknowledge that you:\r\n\t\u2022
    Understand the educational nature and limitations of the software.\r\n\t\u2022
    Accept responsibility for your own learning and safety.\r\n\t\u2022 Agree that
    the simulator does not replace professional driving instruction or certification.\n\r\n6.
    Acceptance\r\nBy proceeding to use the simulator, you agree to these terms and
    understand the scope and limitations of this educational tool.\r\n"
